<article class="env-definition" id="003Y">
  <p><a class="environment-identifier" href="/tag/003Y">Definition <span data-tag="003Y">6.2.1</span>.</a> Let $\mathcal{C}$ be a groupoid such that the set of isomorphism classes is finite, and for any $x\in \mathcal{C}$, the group $\operatorname{Aut}(x)$ is finite. Then we define </p>
  <div class="equation">
  \[  |\mathcal{C}|=\sum _{[x]} \frac{1}{|\operatorname{Aut}(x)|}  \]
</div>
  <p> where the sum is taken over representatives of isomorphism classes in $\mathcal{C}$. </p>
</article>